  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Deborah Weston has given up hope of having a school of her own in New Bedford. Mrs. Ben Congdon may want to have Deborah&apos;s &quot;schoolroom for her daughter.&quot; If Deborah gives up [having a schoolroom] now, she hopes to lose only $5 out of her own pocket. She could have managed a school of forty pupils. Even if her school supports itself during the winter, &quot;I cannot bear to be labouring for nothing as it were-- Money to spend is what I want.&quot; She tells about the troubles of acquaintances.</subfield>
